Help Type: topic
Topic: ai

AI Agent Contract

Primary contract:
  Use Wiki Graph URIs as stable object handles.
  When you have a URI and need valid operations, read `wikigraph help object`.
  When you know an operation and need valid targets, read `wikigraph help verb`.

Object command inputs:
  Never pass a bare filesystem path to URI-targeted commands.
  Convert archive paths into Wiki Graph URIs first:
    /Users/me/book.wikg -> wkg:///Users/me/book.wikg
    ./book.wikg -> wkg://book.wikg

Treat every search result as a Wiki Graph URI.
Search results may use short object URIs such as `wkg://entity/Q8018`; prepend the archive locator before passing them back to object commands:
  wkg:///absolute/path/book.wikg/entity/Q8018

Default exploration loop:
  1. `wikigraph help uri`
  2. `wikigraph help object`
  3. `wikigraph wkg:///absolute/path/book.wikg search <query>`
  4. `wikigraph <located-object-uri> get`
  5. `wikigraph <located-object-uri> related`
  6. `wikigraph <located-object-uri> evidence`
  7. Pick a located chunk or entity URI before `wikigraph <located-graph-object-uri> pack --budget <chars>`

Archive and job commands also use URI targets:
  wikigraph wkg://book.wikg create ./book.md
  wikigraph wkg://book.wikg/state get --json
  wikigraph wkg://book.wikg/chapter/3 queue add --task reading-graph --accept-cost
  wikigraph wkg-job:// list
  wikigraph wkg-job://<job-id> watch --jsonl

Example:
  wikigraph wkg:///Users/me/book.wikg/entity search "朱元璋" --limit 20 --json

Use URI lenses to select searchable object kinds:
  wkg://book.wikg/chapter
  wkg://book.wikg/source
  wkg://book.wikg/summary
  wkg://book.wikg/chunk
  wkg://book.wikg/entity
  wkg://book.wikg/triple
  wkg://book.wikg/chapter/3/entity

Use `--json` or `--jsonl` when a stable machine-readable result is needed.
